    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my wifi router has a solid red light on the \"internet\" icon. i tried turning it off and on but nothing changed. what should i do?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A solid red light on your router's internet icon usually means the router is trying to connect to the internet but failing, or it's stuck in a loop trying to find a signal. It's not just a \"no internet\" situation; it's often a \"I'm trying to find a path but I'm getting lost\" scenario.\n\nFirst, let's check if your modem is actually receiving a signal from your ISP. If your modem has a blinking light, it's likely just waiting for a connection, but if it's solid red, it's probably dead. If your modem is also red, you need to call your ISP immediately.\n\nIf your modem is working but the router is red, you might need to reset the router. This is like a **router's brain getting confused and needing a reboot**. You can do this by holding the reset button on the back of the router for about 10 seconds until the lights start flashing.\n\nIf that doesn't work, try plugging your router into a different outlet or a different wall jack. Sometimes the router is just \"too tired\" to find the signal.\n\nIf you've tried all of this and the light is still solid red, it might be a hardware issue",
